Package nsp

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Disperser
    Interface for generating Coordinates of dispersing propagules.
    ExperimentWriter  
    Mosaic
    A Mosaic represents a linked collection of individual patch objects, allowing for processes that affect their properties as an entire collection.
    MosaicWriter
    Generic interface for reading over Moaic objects and persisting them to output.
    Process
    Interface for handling processes that alter the population in some manner
    RandomGenerator
    Interface for random number generation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Experiment
    This class is used to apply Processes to a Mosaic over time.
    Patch
    Represents a single discrete patch of potential habitat.
    Spread
    Principal class and entry point for running the SPREAD model.
